    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "eb8b7843_81492bd6",
        "filename": "resultdb/cmd/backend/bigquery_export.go",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 169,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-01-08T17:28:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "one problem here is that batchC is not guarantee to close (e.g. it is not `defer close(batchC)`), thus the other goroutine is not guaranteed to exit \u003d\u003e possible goroutine leak.\n\nalternatives:\n1) wrap L143-L167 in a function and do `defer close(batchC)` in the very beginning\n2) same as (1), but in a separate goroutine. The two goroutine can be orchestrated by https://godoc.org/golang.org/x/sync/errgroup#WithContext which cancels the context if either of goroutines exits with an error, thus canceling the other",
      "revId": "dd5b3a6651486871e2516e95fa0e8d6417de1b06",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
